summary: Conversion of Stroti's resource for Oblivion, necessarily re-textured for Skyrim
descriptionHtml:
This is a conversion of Stroti's excellent modder's resource for Oblivion, which can be found here:

https://www.nexusmods.com/oblivion/mods/41086/?

All textures used in the original mod were from Oblivion, and so needed to be replaced.  I have retained the original Oblivion names of the files, but replaced the contents of all of the files either with vanilla (or Bethesda high-res) Skyrim textures, modified as needed, or ones from the following modder's resources:

Tamira's conversions of Stroti mods - Manor:  https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36386/?
     Castle Wall:  https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/33948/?
     Old Mill:  https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/37176/?

Aj47951's Rock Texture Set:  https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/6987/?

Mr. Dave's Texture Resource:  https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/2324/?

Thomas/GoblinVomit's Imperial Mages Guild sign banner and symbol:  https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/64272/?


There is a small demo esp included if you want to see what the houses look like in-game.  Simply type:

cow CWSiegeTestWorld 0 0

You might land inside a house or the well, so type don't forget to type tcl if you need to get unstuck!

I have converted one of the doors to work as a load door instead of merely a static, and will be doing the rest eventually for my upcoming Daggerfall mod!
author: Stroti
